# Git Workflow (Git 工作流)

Scope: all DTS repositories

## Branch Strategy

- `main` — production-ready, protected. Only merge via PR.
- `develop` — integration branch. Feature branches merge here first.
- `feature/<service>/<description>` — feature work. Example: `feature/dts-agent/intent-routing`
- `fix/<service>/<description>` — bug fixes.
- `release/vX.Y.Z` — release preparation.

## Commit Convention

Format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`

Types: feat, fix, refactor, test, docs, chore, ci, perf
Scope: service name (dts-agent, dts-platform, dts-operator, etc.)

Examples:
- `feat(dts-agent): add multi-step reasoning with LangGraph`
- `fix(dts-data-security): enforce row-level filtering on vector search`
- `test(dts-ontology-store): add integration tests for type CRUD`

## PR Rules

- Every PR requires at least 1 reviewer approval.
- All CI checks must pass (lint, build, test).
- PR description must reference the task ID from worklog.
- Squash merge to develop. Regular merge to main.
- No force push to main or develop.

## Monorepo vs Multi-repo

- Decision deferred to implementation planning phase.
- Regardless of repo structure, each service maintains independent build and test.
